      <heading>Fri Jul  6 (Lee the Bartender) :: The Ramblin' Rose</heading>
      <slot>2</slot>
      <level>203</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>They burned my bar, they did!  The bastards just burned it right down! One
moment I was minding my own business, serving fine ales, and the next...
Light!  Whitecloaks dead everywhere, those Asha'men fellows running about
playing with fires and freezing men in their tracks, and before I can even
gather my wits, I'm standing outside watching the roof fall in!  I'll tell
you right now, it's a sad day in Caemlyn.  Next thing we know, things'll
be right back where they were the last few years, with bits of our city
going up in flames every night.  I hate to say it, but sometimes those darn
Whitecloaks have the right of it...  this city draws trouble like it truly
did lay under the Shadow!
Anyway, I'll be darned if I put up with this much longer...  I think I'll
go live with my sister in the country.  I figure they could use a barman
at the Inn in my folks old town...  And you should do the same.  It's not
safe for plain folks in this town any longer.
</text>
