      <heading>Sun Aug  5 (Rand)       :: &amp;WAn official looking decree.&amp;n</heading>
      <slot>4</slot>
      <level>170</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>In an effort to promote better relations with the Aes Sedai, I have
decided to lessen the restrictions against women channeling in Caemlyn.
Any Aes Sedai who wishes to be able to channel freely in this city
should report to the Captain of the Queen's Guard. Her name and
description will be taken down and passed to those whose duty it is to
enforce this law. The Aes Sedai must wear her ring and shawl openly if
she wishes to have freedom to channel. Any woman who is not an Aes
Sedai, but who wishes to be allowed to channel, should also report to
the Captain. She will be given an armband to signify that she has
complied with the law and is allowed to channel. It will also serve to
identify her to the Asha'man who enforce this decree. The Aiel Wise
Ones are known to me already. As they are quite distinctive, they will
be required to wear no further emblems and are considered to already
have complied with this law. Any woman who channels without wearing the
outward signs of compliance shall be captured and incarcerated. She
shall also be held fully responsible for any consequences of resisting
arrest. Any man, other than myself, who channels without wearing the
black coat of the Asha'man shall be captured if possible or killed if
necessary. 
Rand al'Thor
The Dragon
---------------------------------------------------------------------------
OOC NOTE:
Any woman who wishes to channel in Caemlyn without being arrested
should mail both myself and Kaliendrick a brief letter informing us of
such. She should then include in her doing whenever IC that she is
wearing her ring and shawl or if not an aes sedai that she has the 
white silk strip emblazoned with a dragon tied around her upper left
arm. Any man that wishes to channel in Caemlyn without severe penalties
should join the Asha'man.
</text>
