      <slot>6</slot>
      <level>170</level>
      <author>0</author>
      <date>0</date>
      <text>&amp;rBlood&amp;n splattered walls and seared overturned tables greeted
the Queen's guard two days passed as the second common room of the
Half Moon Inn was said to have suddenly burst with a loud explosion
sending shards of glass into the streets of Caemlyn.

Witnesses say two guardsman responded promptly to reports and 
thundered into the Half Moon Inn with swords readied, only to
meet their fate at a second explosion which took their lives 
sending armor and flesh throughout the inn. The entry way to 
the second common room reportedly collapsed and guardsman worked
rigorously to clear the debris to check for survivors. To the 
disheartened guardsman, there were no survivors.

Witnesses mention seeing a bright flash of light through the 
broken windows just before the second group of guardsman arrived
at the scene.

</text>
